description: {"blocks":[{"key":"fb1dh","text":"Cleavage Under Targets \u0026 Release Using Nuclease (CUT\u0026RUN) is a revolutionary genomic mapping strategy developed by the group of Dr. Steven Henikoff. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"427m9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dh1fl","text":"In CUT\u0026RUN, cells or nuclei are immobilized to a solid support, with pAG-MNase cleaved DNA fragments isolated from solution. The workflow is compatible with next-generation sequencing (NGS) to provide high quality genome-wide profiles of histone post-translational modifications (PTMs) and chromatin-associated proteins (e.g. TFs and chromatin remodelers)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cd3v8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"58huj","text":"Historically, ChIP-seq is the leading approach for genome-wide mapping of histone PTMs and chromatin-associated proteins. 50) Select appropriate IlluminaÂ®sequencing platform (see Appendix I) based on the number of CUT&RUN libraries and desired sequencing depth.
*IMPORTANT:In contrast to ChIP-seq, only 3-8 million paired-end reads per reaction areneeded for adequate CUT&RUN coverage. For low abundance targets (e.g.H3K4me3), aim for 3-5 million reads. For high abundance targets (e.g.H3K27me3), aim for 5-8 million.
51) Pool libraries at desired ratios using the molarity calculations from Section VI (200-700 bp region) and load onto IlluminaÂ®sequencer. General steps:
a. Dilute each library to the same nM concentration, depending on final yields.For NextSeq 2000 and NextSeq 500/550, dilute to 1-4 nM.
b. Pool equimolar libraries into one tube.
c. Dilute pooled libraries to appropriate concentration and in the volume required for IlluminaÂ®platform. Follow guidelines from specific IlluminaÂ®kit to load onto sequencer (support.illumina.com).
d. When setting up a multiplexed sequencing run, make sure dual i5 & i7 barcodes are correctly assigned for each library (seeImportant, below). For a full list of NGS indexes in an easy-to-copy format, see the CUTANATM Library Prep Multiplexing Primers Excel spreadsheet atepicypher.com/14-1001.
